\caption{Chern-Simons number auto-correlation function $ \frac{1}{Q_s^3 V} \langle (N_{CS}(t+\delta t)- N_{CS}(t))^2 \rangle$ as a function of the temporal separation $\delta t$ starting from $Q_s t=50$ during the non-equilibrium evolution. Different curves in each panel  correspond to different lattice volumes $Q_s^3 V=96^3,128^3,196^3$ for cooling depth $Q_s^2\tau_c=12$ (top) and $Q_s^3 V=64^3,96^3$ for  $Q_s^2\tau_c=324$ (bottom).}
\label{correlations}
