\caption{Comparison of Chern-Simons number measurements using the calibrated cooling ($\tau_c=0.75~(g^2T)^{-2}$) and slave field techniques for a single configuration in thermal equilibrium ($N=24$, $\beta=2$).  Slave field results are shifted by 5 units for comparison purposes.  The difference between the two methods is small over the course of the entire simulation.}
